Added a function that wrap a Throwable in a Result

When ending an attemptXYZ operation with .orSkip the failure is not
stored in the repository (as is the intention). To route the failure
back into a repository of Result .orEnd needs to be used, and the
Throwable needs to be wrapped in a Result. This function does exactly
that.

Added missing Repository bindWith unit test

Also bumped coverage of Result
Tidied up some unused test code

Changed BaseObservable to survive rotation

If LAST_REMOVED is sent when FIRST_ADDED is queued, both are instead
removed. Re-activating a repository within the same loop have no value
and in this way a global repository can survive device rotation.
